SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 353
By Rose
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Dr. John Combs, 2025
Tennessee Coordinated School Health
Superintendent of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those outstanding educational leaders who have devoted their careers to providing
the highest-quality care for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Dr. John Combs, Superintendent of Tipton County Schools, is one such
exceptional individual, who has distinguished himself as a professional of the greatest
dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Combs was recently named the 2025 Coordinated School Health
Superintendent of the Year by the Tennessee Department of Education, a most befitting honor
that recognizes the positive influence he has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Coordinated School Health connects physical, emotional, and
social health with education through eight interrelated components; this coordinated approach
improves students' health and their capacity to learn through the support of families,
communities, and schools working together; and
WHEREAS, Dr. John Combs has ably served Tipton County Schools for more than three
decades, including as superintendent since 2018 and previously as director of instruction, TIF
grant administrator, principal, counselor, and teacher; and
WHEREAS, he holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Secondary Education and
Teaching from Freed-Hardeman University, a Master of Education degree in School
Administration and Supervision from the University of Memphis, and a Doctor of Education
degree in Educational Leadership and Administration from Trevecca Nazarene University; and
